  "fixture": "co_pretrigger",
  "edition": 11,
  "rng_seed": 42,
  "transition_to_phase": 10,
  "disable_ai": true,
  "description": "Regression for the Consolidate-step visibility guard: after the final fight the right-panel FightResolutionDock deliberately lingers on its 'Done' summary (the player never pressed Done \u2014 the common case). Unlike the old FightSequenceDialog bottom pop-up, the dock lives in the right panel so it never covers the battlefield; this scenario asserts the dock is still active on its summary, then enters the Consolidate step and asserts FightController._dismiss_blocking_fight_dialogs deactivated it (its job is done) and cleared any stray AttackAssignmentDialog, so the ConsolidationStepPanel picker and the bottom-docked ConsolidateDialog open over a clear board. Setup-only privileges (CP zeroed, wounds inflated for deterministic aliveness) mirror the sibling scenario; every in-game decision is a real click or drag.",
